<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Resource Groups on Luiz Macedo</title><link>https://luizmacedo.dev/en/tags/resource-groups/</link><description>Recent content in Resource Groups on Luiz Macedo</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><copyright>Copyright © 2023–2026 LUIZ MACEDO'S BLOG is licensed under CC BY 4.0</copyright><lastBuildDate>Wed, 03 Feb 2021 11:00:17 -0600</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://luizmacedo.dev/en/tags/resource-groups/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Azure Devops Service Tag NSG Rule</title><link>https://luizmacedo.dev/en/posts/azure-devops-service-tag-nsg-rule/</link><pubDate>Wed, 03 Feb 2021 11:00:17 -0600</pubDate><guid>https://luizmacedo.dev/en/posts/azure-devops-service-tag-nsg-rule/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;If you need to enable the Service Tags for your NSG or Firewall pointing to the Azure DevOps Service tag, run:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="ln"&gt; 1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;az network nsg rule create -g MYRESOURCEGROUP &lt;span class="se"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="ln"&gt; 2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; --nsg-name MYNSG &lt;span class="se"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="ln"&gt; 3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; -n AzureDevOps &lt;span class="se"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="ln"&gt; 4&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; --priority &lt;span class="m"&gt;400&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="se"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="ln"&gt; 5&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; --source-address-prefixes VirtualNetwork &lt;span class="se"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="ln"&gt; 6&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; --destination-address-prefixes Storage &lt;span class="se"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="ln"&gt; 7&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; --destination-port-ranges &lt;span class="s1"&gt;&amp;#39;*&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="se"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="ln"&gt; 8&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; --direction Inbound &lt;span class="se"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="ln"&gt; 9&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; --access Allow &lt;span class="se"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="ln"&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; --protocol Tcp &lt;span class="se"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="ln"&gt;11&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; --description &lt;span class="s2"&gt;&amp;#34;Allow Azure DevOps Services.&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Service Tag does not apply to Microsoft Hosted Agents. Customers are still required to allow the entire geography for the Microsoft Hosted Agents. If allowing the entire geography is a concern, we recommend using the Azure Virtual Machine Scale Set Agents. The Scale Set Agents are a form of self-hosted agents that can be autoscaled to meet your demands.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>